Code Style Guide
This document outlines the coding standards followed in this project to ensure readability, maintainability, and consistency.

General Guidelines
Follow the KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid) and DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principles.
Write code that is clear, concise, and self-explanatory.
Each class or method should have a single responsibility. Avoid large classes or methods that do too much.
Java Coding Style
1. Indentation
Use 4 spaces for indentation. Do not use tabs.
2. Line Length
Maximum line length is 100 characters. Break lines logically where appropriate, such as after commas or before operators.
